      <hedline>
        <hl1>Oyster Bay Development: Moratorium Debate . . .</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Laury I Weber letter on Councilman Anthony D Macagnone's July 30 letter questions why he has changed mind about need to protect water supply in Oyster Bay, Long Island (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In his letter, Mr. Macagnone contradicted his previous endorsement of Councilwoman Eisler's proposal.</p>
        <p>Mr. Macagnone supported this agenda in his election campaign and used Ms. Eisler's volunteers and her campaign mailings to help his election. At a fund-raiser at my home, he stated flatly that a master plan for the town is sorely needed, and agreed that to allow construction could impair our water supply.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>In his letter, Mr. Macagnone contradicted his previous endorsement of Councilwoman Eisler's proposal.</p>
        <p>Mr. Macagnone supported this agenda in his election campaign and used Ms. Eisler's volunteers and her campaign mailings to help his election. At a fund-raiser at my home, he stated flatly that a master plan for the town is sorely needed, and agreed that to allow construction could impair our water supply.</p>
        <p>What new information does he have that a moratorium is not a proper thing to do at this time?</p>
        <p>LAURY I. WEBER  Woodbury</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
